<subSubSection pageId="226" pageNumber="227" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 197" captionStartId="F197" captionText="Figure 197. Distribution of Conostegia subpeltata." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure197" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96555" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">197</figureCitation>
). Endemic to Costa Rica where it is known from the Caribbean slope of the Guanacaste and Talamanca mountain ranges at (100-)900-1200 m.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Zenodo-Dep="974053" doi="10.3897/phytokeys.67.6703.figure197" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/96555" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" start="Figure 197" startId="F197">
<paragraph pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Figure 197.</emphasis>
Distribution of 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph pageId="226" pageNumber="227">
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a very distinctive species because of its slightly peltate leaves, well defined stellate trichomes on the leaves and hypanthia, axillary inflorescences, and 4-merous flowers with a calyx that is fused in bud and ruptures irregularly into unequal lobes. The flowers of this species resemble the common morphology on section 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Geniculatae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Geniculatae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with bright yellow anthers and exserted styles. This species is known from very few specimens but surprisingly these few specimens come from two mountain ranges, one in Volcan Miravalles in Guanacaste and the other from the Talamanca mountain range (Tapanti National Park and Hitoy Cerere Biological Reserve). 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forms a well supported species pair with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia colliculosa" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="colliculosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia colliculosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the molecular phylogeny. This species pair is in turn sister to 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel &amp; Almeda" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia subpeltata" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subpeltata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia subpeltata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easily distinguished from both of these close relatives by the subpeltate leaves and axillary inflorescences. It shares the 4-merous flowers with 
<taxonomicName authority="Kriebel, 2016" authorityName="Kriebel" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Kriebel" baseAuthorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Conostegia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Conostegia calocoma" order="Myrtales" pageId="226" pageNumber="227" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocoma">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="226" pageNumber="227">Conostegia calocoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
